South Africa  is culling as many as
5,700 ostriches to prevent the spread of avian flu, The New Age
reported, citing Anton Kruger of the South African Ostrich
Business Chamber.  So far, the virus has only been found on one farm, the
Johannesburg-based newspaper said, citing Kruger. It didnâ€™t say
